org.jimmutable.core.objects

Class TransientImmutableObject<T extends TransientImmutableObject<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jimmutable.core.objects.TransientObject<T>
      • org.jimmutable.core.objects.TransientImmutableObject<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<T>

    public abstract class TransientImmutableObject<T extends TransientImmutableObject<T>>
extends TransientObject<T>
    An abstract base class for standard objects that want to guarantee immutability.

    A standard immutable object may only be modified before it is complete.

    Note: It is important that the normalization code goes into TransientObject.normalize(), the validation code into TransientObject.validate(), and the freezing code into freeze(). The latter is particularly important as deep cloning (and hence building) rely upon the ability to control the timing of these operations.

    Author:
    Jim Kane

      • freeze

        public abstract void freeze()
        Make any changes to this object required to make this object immutable. Frequently the only job of freeze is to call freeze() on any non-primative fields.
        See Also:
        Field.freeze()

      • complete

        public void complete()
        Declare that an object is ready to use. In addition to normal complete(), freeze() is called to toggle immutability.

        isComplete() is guaranteed to return true after complete has returned.

        complete can only be called once for immutable objects. Future invocations will result in an ImmutableException.

        Overrides:
        complete in class TransientObject<T extends TransientImmutableObject<T>>
        Throws:
        ImmutableException - if the object is complete
